parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric power brake booster can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking capability, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes straight to the floorboard
the brake pedal is extremely hard
the warning light comes on and goes off
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the brakes fail at highway speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, increased emissions, and potentially cause engine failure, resulting in costly repairs and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine oil level drops rapidly
the oil warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the engine makes unusual noises or knocking sounds
the engine emits excessive smoke or exhaust fumes
the vehicle's fuel efficiency decreases.
